gmd:description.gco:CharacterString:
EX_1 Multisurface with 2 disjoint polygons and 1 that intersects with the main polygon(the one with the hole). Should be reconstructed after round trip as 1 polygon with hole and 1 polygons without hole
should be inclusion.
Also has a BBOX that should be ignored after re-construction

EX_2 A large include polygon and a small exclude polygon that fully intersects the include polygon
should be an include polygon with a hole

EX_3 A large include polygon and another small include polygon that fully intersects the large polygon
should result in one inclusion polygon

EX_4 A large EXCLUDE polygon and another small EXCLUDE polygon that fully intersects the large polygon
should result in one exclude polygon

EX_5 A large polygon and another small polygon that fully intersects the large polygon Neither specify include or exclude
should result in two include polygons

EX_6 A large include polygon and another large exclude polygon that fully disjoint from the large polygon
should result in one include polygon

EX_7 A large include polygon and another large include polygon that fully disjoint from the large polygon
should result in two include polygons

EX_8 A large exclude polygon and another large exclude polygon that fully disjoint from the large polygon
should result in two exclude polygons

EX_9 2 disjoint exclude polygons, 1 include polygon that intersects both
should result in one include polygon

EX_10 A large exclude polygon and a small include polygon that fully intersects the exclude polygon
should be an exclude polygon with a hole
EX_11 Should result in 2 BBox elements
EX_15 Merging 2 geometries should result in 1 polygons in the multipolygon because they touch
